Vice President Kamala Harris and Labor Secretary Marty Walsh held a roundtable discussion with young worker organizers to discuss their efforts to organize unions and inspire workers across the country to join or organize unions. President Biden also joined the discussion and thanked the organizers for their leadership. The worker organizers shared their stories and motivations for organizing, including fair pay, benefits, and respect in the workplace. The Biden-Harris Administration reaffirmed its support for unions and emphasized the importance of worker power in rebuilding the economy. The attendees represented various industries, including warehousing, animation, and retail.